com.ibm.team.repository.common.query
Interface IQueryPage

All Known Subinterfaces:
IDataQueryPage, IItemQueryPage, ITextQueryPage
public interface IQueryPage

Represents the abstract definition of a paged query result. There are two kinds of queries (and thus two kinds of query results):

  • Item Queries - retrieves a list of IItems based on some filter criteria
  • Data Queries - retrieves a list of data rows, where the individual fields that comprise a row may be values from one or more IItems, or computed values

A query page is single page of query results, where a page is a chunk of a total result set. Paging is used to manage the processing of query results in a manner that protects system memory and response size. Additionally the query page has information unique to a given query invocation, such as the total result size and a token that is a key to retrieve other pages of the query result.

Since:
0.5
See Also:
IItemQueryPage, IDataQueryPage

Method Detail

getStartPosition

int getStartPosition()
Answers the zero-based start position of this page relative to the full result set

Returns:
int start position of this page relative to the full result; zero for the first page; never negative; always less than the size of entire result.

getNextStartPosition

int getNextStartPosition()
Answers the zero-based start position of the page that immediately succeeds this page, or -1 if this page is the last page of the result.

Returns:
int the start position of the next page in the result set, if it exists; never zero; will be -1 if this is the last page.
See Also:
IQueryPage.hasNext()

getSize

int getSize()
Answers the size of this query result page. The server determines the size to return, regardless of the hint provided by the requesting client. The server may throttle the returned size to manage resources. The page size returned will never exceed the size specified by the client, but it may be less; however, all pages in a result will always be the same size, except for the last page. If the page is the last page in the query result, then the size will be the count of the remainder items in that last page. Clients iterating through a page should always check the size as part of iterating through the elements in a page.

Returns:
non-negative int value; may be zero if the result is empty

getResultSize

int getResultSize()
Total size of the result of the query. This is equivalent to the sum of the sizes of all pages. This value will remain the same for all pages of a given query execution.

Returns:
non-negative int value; may be zero if the result is empty

hasNext

boolean hasNext()
Indicates if there are more results on the server beyond this page. Attempts to fetch additional pages starting from a page that is at the end of the result set will result in an exception from the server.

Returns:
true if this is not the last page; otherwise false

getToken

UUID getToken()
Provides the token that uniquely identifies the executed query. Used for subsequent retrievals of pages from the query result. This value will remain the same for all pages of a given query execution.

Returns:
a unique system generated UUID
